Package: vrpr
Title: Vehicle Routing Problem Solver (PyVRP for R)
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("First", "Last", email = "leite@de.ufpe.br",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = "TODO: preencher nome do(a) mantenedor(a)"),
    person(family = "PyVRP contributors", role = c("ctb", "cph"),
           comment = "Autores do nucleo C++ PyVRP vendorizado (MIT)")
  )
Description: A high-performance, tidyverse-style interface to vehicle routing
    problem (VRP) solving. Ports the PyVRP C++ core to R via cpp11, with no
    Python runtime dependency. Supports capacitated VRP, time windows, multiple
    depots, heterogeneous fleets and prize-collecting variants, driven by an
    iterated local search metaheuristic.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/StrategicProjects/vrpr
BugReports: https://github.com/StrategicProjects/vrpr/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Depends:
    R (>= 4.3)
Imports:
    cli,
    rlang,
    stats,
    tibble,
    vctrs
LinkingTo:
    cpp11
Suggests:
    reticulate,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    withr
